## Canonical baseline (repo)

Before drafting `slides_spec.json` or `slides_spec_vN.json`, read **`docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-baseline-slides-spec.md`**, **`docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-v30-slide-inventory.md`**, and **`docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-v30-typography.md`** (measured fonts, **2.8in** body box height, **12pt** section primary line, **`text_boxes[].paragraphs`** for native bullets and PESTEL **Product implication:** highlight). The reference **`~/Downloads/GCC_Recruiting_PMF_Roadmap_v30.pptx`** is **50 slides** with blocks often dropped in later specs: **Research Author**, **Competitive SWOT** (3rd competitive slide), **four** Win/Loss slides, **four** Ideation Hub slides (when CSV exists), **Full Funnel** diagnostic, recurring **section dividers**. **Target 48–52** slides in the JSON array (v30 parity); if the MCP **auto-agenda** adds +1 in `.pptx`, account for it. Do **not** clone only the latest **`slides_spec_v*.json`** without re-inserting those **content classes**—that causes drift from v30. Do **not** ship fewer than **36 slides** (hard minimum) or omit standard sections unless the PM explicitly requests a **focus deck**.

## MCP Workflow

1. Call `parse_template` for `template_path`
2. Write slide spec JSON to `slides_spec.json` (or `slides_spec_vN.json`) at project root
3. Call `create_presentation` or run `generate_presentation.py`
4. Output to `~/Downloads/[Country]_Recruiting_PMF_Roadmap_vN.pptx` — version auto-increments on each generation (v1, v2, v3…)

### Auto-agenda slide (slide 2) — **no code on screen**

The Slide Deck MCP **injects** an agenda immediately after the TITLE slide. The engine derives lines from your spec (typically **Section Title** slides and/or slide titles). **Known failure mode:** if a **`paragraphs[].text`** field is a **JSON array of run objects** (e.g. `[{"text":"PESTEL","font_size_pt":11,"color":"laptop"}]`), some builds **`str()` that list** into the agenda shape → the audience sees Python-like `[{'text': 'PESTEL', ...}]` instead of readable copy.

**Mandatory (Section Title / divider slides):**

1. **Agenda-driving subtitle (second paragraph):** Use **`"text": "<plain string>"`** only for the **subtitle** line (the `laptop` de-emphasised line under **Workday Confidential**). **Never** use a run-array there. This is the line that populates the exec agenda; it must render as normal text.
2. **Primary line (`Workday Confidential`):** Prefer a **plain string** for `"text"` as well if your engine build still leaks run-arrays into the agenda; otherwise a single-run array is acceptable only after you confirm the generated `.pptx` agenda is clean.
3. **Substance, not stubs:** Each subtitle must read like a **v30 exec agenda row**: **12–22 words**, **`Section | Substance`** pattern (pipe optional but encouraged), stating **what evidence** the audience will see next — not two-word labels (`PESTEL`, `Win / Loss` alone are **non-compliant**).

**Examples (compliant subtitles, plain string):**

- `Research challenge | Research questions, objectives, and Braun & Clarke five-phase methodology for GCC Recruiting PMF`
- `PESTEL | Political, economic, social, technological, environmental, and legal factors with yellow-highlight product implications`
- `Primary research | Interview programme, participant roster, per-customer findings, and ideation quant where data exists`

**Checklist:** Open the output `.pptx` slide 2; if any line contains `[{` or `'text':`, revise **Section Title** `paragraphs` to plain-string `text` and richer copy, then regenerate.

## Slide spec schema (mandatory — matches `user-slide-deck-mcp` `create_presentation`)

- Use **`layout_name`** on every slide (e.g. `"TITLE"`, `"Title Only"`, `"Title Only_Alt"`, `"Section Title"`, `"1/2 Headline_Alt"`, `"Bumper Slide"`). Do **not** use a top-level `"layout"` key; the engine ignores it and may render every slide as a title slide.
- **`placeholders`** must map indices to objects: `"0": {"text": "Title"}`. Never use `"0": "plain string"`.
- **Section Title** has no title placeholder. Match **v30 typography**: one **`text_box`** at **`(3.3, 1.5)`**, **5.6 × 2.2** in, with **`paragraphs`**: primary line **12pt bold** `ink` (e.g. `S E C T I O N  0 1` or `Workday Confidential`); secondary line **11pt** `laptop` at **level 0** (no bullet — avoid `level > 0` on the subtitle or the engine adds a `•`). Do **not** use **24pt** section headings; that drifts from v30. **Auto-agenda:** the **subtitle** `text` MUST be a **plain string** (see **Auto-agenda slide** above); use substantive **12–22 word** copy, not section stubs.
- **Body content:** Prefer **`text_boxes[].paragraphs`** with **`level`: 1** for bullets (native `•`) instead of a single **`text`** string with Unicode bullet characters. Default body box: **`left_inches` 0.7, `top_inches` 1.2, `width_inches` 8.6, `height_inches` 2.8** (see **`gcc-pmf-roadmap-v30-typography.md`**). Per-paragraph and per-run formatting supports **`font_size_pt`**, **`bold`**, **`highlight`** (e.g. PESTEL **Product implication:** `FFFF00`).

## Deck structure (target length 48–52 slides for v30 parity; minimum 36; McKinsey-style tone)

**MANDATORY: Every new versioned deck MUST include ALL sections below unless user explicitly requests a "focus deck."**

1. **Title + Research Author + Executive Summary** (**v30 parity: 3–4 slides**)
   - Title: [Region] Recruiting Product-Market Fit Research
   - Section divider (optional; v30 uses “Workday Confidential” between major blocks)
   - **Research Author** (ownership, date, data sources) — **mandatory** for v30 match
   - Executive Summary: Key themes, PESTEL headlines, roadmap/E2E headline

2. **SECTION: Research Challenge** (3 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Research Challenge | Objectives and methodology"
   - Research Question & Objectives
   - 5-Phase Framework (Braun & Clarke phases 0–6)

3. **SECTION: Context Review** (2+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Context Review | Strategic context and market momentum"
   - Strategic Context (market size, growth, digital transformation)

4. **SECTION: PESTEL Analysis** (7 slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "PESTEL Analysis | Political, Economic, Social, Technological, Environmental, Legal"
   - Political (full slide with nationalization mandates, penalties)
   - Economic (full slide with market data, CAGR, investment trends)
   - Social (full slide with communication channel stats, smartphone penetration, cultural factors)
   - Technological (full slide with AI, government portals, integrations)
   - Environmental (full slide, DATA GAP if no recruiting signal)
   - Legal (full slide with PDPL, interview regulations, compliance requirements)

   **v30 depth (PESTEL body — do not ship sparse slides):** Each of the **six** factor slides must match **golden v30 density**, not a 3-bullet stub. Before `create_presentation`, verify **every** PESTEL slide meets **all** of:
   - **Bullet count:** Minimum **six** substantive bullet paragraphs at **level 1** *before* the **Product implication:** paragraph. If the **120** report is thin on one factor, add **level 2** sub-bullets under 2–3 parents so the slide still reads as **full** (do not pad with filler; pull from PESTEL desk research in the report or mark a controlled **DATA GAP** sub-bullet and expand detail in `speaker_notes`).
   - **Anchors:** At least **three** of those bullets must include a **concrete anchor** transcribed from **120** (named law, programme, regulator, year, **%**, **currency + magnitude**, portal name, or article citation). If the markdown truly lacks anchors for that factor, one bullet must state the gap explicitly and speaker notes must carry the source hunt.
   - **Hierarchy:** On **at least four** of the six slides, include **one cluster** of **level 2** sub-bullets (minimum **two** children) for nuance (e.g. enforcement, tenant variance, product boundary).
   - **Product implication:** One closing paragraph (**level 0**, run-formatted per typography doc) with **minimum ~22 words**, **two clauses** (factor context → **specific** recruiting product action). **No** one-line slogans or fragments; match the explanatory weight of **`GCC_Recruiting_PMF_Roadmap_v30.pptx`** PESTEL slides.
   - **Speaker notes:** Minimum **five** presenter bullets (story, caveats, “if challenged”) plus **References:** with working URLs — PESTEL is exec-facing; notes carry overflow detail if the 2.8in box is at capacity.

5. **SECTION: Competitive Landscape** (**3** content slides + section divider — **v30 parity**)
   - Section Title: "Competitive Landscape | Regional specialists vs global platforms"
   - Regional specialists (1 slide)
   - Global platforms (1 slide)
   - **SWOT** — Workday Recruiting in region (1 slide) — **mandatory** unless focus deck

6. **SECTION: Win/Loss Overview** (**4** content slides + section divider — **v30 parity**)
   - Section Title: "Win/Loss Overview | [Region]-explicit gaps"
   - Dataset overview
   - Top N gap themes (severity-weighted; table or chart)
   - Gap analysis charts (bar/stacked per **110** chart rules)
   - GCC-relevant / proxy severity gaps (table)

7. **SECTION: Primary Research** (section divider + **interviews + quant** — **v30 parity**)
   - Section Title: "Primary Research | Interview participants"
   - Strip intro (e.g. participant count, date range)
   - Interview Participants (P1, P2, P3 with roles and companies)
   - One slide per customer: P1, P2, P3… (quotes + themes)
   - **Customer Ideation Hub / CSV** — **4 slides** when idea or opportunity data exists: overview (counts); top areas by volume (chart/table); key themes from verbatims; AI ideas spotlight (or equivalent). If no CSV, insert **DATA GAP** slide — do not skip the **content class** without PM “focus deck” approval.

   **v30 depth (Primary research / customer interview slides — do not ship theme stubs):**
   - **Strip intro slide (“Customer Interviews | …”):** Minimum **six** **level 1** bullets covering: population / **n**; **GCC** (or country) relevance; **date range** or wave; **method** (e.g. semi-structured, Braun & Clarke tie-in); **data sources** (transcript paths, SME note if any); **how** interviews triangulate with CSV, Win/Loss, and PESTEL. Optional **level 2** bullets for limitations — still counts toward density.
   - **Participants table slide:** Keep table; if the report adds **hiring volume**, **req scale**, or **tooling** context per participant, add a **small** **level 1** bullet list (2–4 bullets) *below* or in an adjacent `text_box` only if the MCP layout supports it without crushing the table — otherwise put overflow in **speaker notes** (minimum **five** bullets for this slide).
   - **One slide per customer (P1, P2, P3…):** Minimum **seven** bullet lines **in aggregate** across **level 1 + level 2** (e.g. 5×L1 + 2×L2). At least **two** bullets must be **quote-led**: start with a **short verbatim** (smart quotes, ≤30 words) from the transcript, then a dash or colon and the insight, ending with **`(P1, Organisation)`** style attribution consistent with **010** anonymisation. At least **one** bullet must **name** a **validated theme** (or theme number) from **120**. At least **one** bullet must express a **JTBD-style** hiring job in one line (*When …, I want …, so I can …*). Remaining bullets synthesise **pain, workarounds, volume, compliance**, and **product hooks** as in **v30** — not single-word labels.
   - **Speaker notes (per-customer slides):** Minimum **five** presenter bullets (which theme to stress, follow-up quotes, contradictions, commercial tone) plus **References:** transcript filename or path from the report.

8. **SECTION: Thematic Analysis** (4+ slides with section divider)
   - Section Title: "Thematic Analysis | Validated themes and triangulation"
   - Validated Themes 1-3 (or 1-4 if >6 themes)
   - Validated Themes 4-6 (or 5-7 if >7 themes)
   - Cross-Source Validation Matrix (triangulation table: Theme | P1 | P2 | P3 | CSV | PMF Impact)
   - **Do not** replace this compact split with many single-theme deep-dive slides **without** PM approval — it breaks v30 length and rhythm

8a. **SECTION: Full Funnel / Gap Diagnostic** (**1–2 slides** — **v30 parity**)
   - e.g. “GCC Recruiting Gap Analysis - Full Funnel” (funnel or diagnostic chart — use Win/Loss + interview evidence)

9. **SECTION: Roadmap Recommendations** (N + handoff; **v30 used 6** rec slides — if report has **8**, add slides and trim optional deep dives or accept ~52–54 with PM approval)
   - Section Title: "Roadmap Recommendations | Priority 1 and Priority 2"
   - Recommendation 1: [Title] (5-part: Problem, Evidence, Recommendation, Why now, Success Metrics)
   - Recommendation 2–6+ as in report
   - E2E Handoff: N Recommendations for PM Selection (numbered table slide)

10. **Bumper Slide**

**Canonical baseline enforcement:** `slides_spec.json` MUST implement the **content classes** above and match **`docs/decks/gcc-pmf-roadmap-v30-slide-inventory.md`** for GCC full PMF decks. When generating versioned decks, the agent MUST:
1. Prefer **v30 inventory** as skeleton, not only the previous **`slides_spec_v*.json`**
2. Populate with content from the **120** report
3. Add version-specific deep-dive slides **only** after standard sections (or with PM approval to trade depth vs length)
4. Never skip or compress **SWOT, 4× Win/Loss, Ideation block (or DATA GAP), Full Funnel, Research Author** unless user says **focus deck only**

**Compressed decks are forbidden by default.** If a full PMF deck has **<48 slides** while claiming v30 parity, or is missing the **v30 content classes** above, it violates the standard (hard floor remains **≥36** slides minimum for any “full” deck).

**Participant Anonymization:** Use **P1, P2, P3** consistently on participant and quote slides (match **120** report).

**Recommendation slide structure (5-part):** Problem | Evidence | Recommendation | Why now | Success Metrics

**Speaker Notes (MANDATORY for content slides):**
- Add `speaker_notes` to every content slide except TITLE, Section Title, Bumper Slide
- Format: Bullet-pointed presenter guidance, then "References:" with live, working URLs
- Include references for all sources used (Mondaq, Astute Analytica, Braun & Clarke, etc.)

**Product Implication (PESTEL slides):**
- Each PESTEL slide ends with **Product implication:** — **11pt bold**, yellow highlight **`FFFF00`** on the implication line (per **`010-style-guide.mdc`**). Implement with **`paragraphs`** + run-level **`highlight`**: `"FFFF00"` (see **`gcc-pmf-roadmap-v30-typography.md`**). The implication text must meet the **~22-word / two-clause** minimum in the **PESTEL v30 depth** block above.

**Chart requirements:**
- **One label per bar:** Use exactly one series for simple bar charts (e.g. Win/Loss Top 10). For stacked bars (e.g. Ideation Hub), use `bar_stacked`.
- **Font sizes:** Always include `category_axis_font_size_pt: 9`, `value_axis_font_size_pt: 9`, `title_font_size_pt: 10`.

**Table requirements:**
- **Font size:** 7–9pt for table content (7pt for dense SWOT)
- **Headers:** Navy background (`ink`) with white text (`paper`)
- **Header height:** `header_height_inches: 0.25` for compact headers
- **SWOT:** Two separate tables (Strengths/Weaknesses at `top_inches: 1.0`, Opportunities/Threats at `top_inches: 3.15`), `height_inches: 2.1` each

**Content positioning:**
- Body text: `top_inches: 1.2` (not 1.6)
- Tables: Start at `top_inches: 0.95` or `1.0` where possible

